# CMMS Platform - Checklist Feature Implementation Plan

**Project:** CMMS (Computerized Maintenance Management System) Platform  
**Document Type:** Technical Implementation Plan  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** March 27, 2026  
**Status:** Draft  

---

## 1. Executive Summary

This document outlines the comprehensive implementation plan for adding a **Checklist Feature** to the CMMS Platform. The feature enables users to define, track, and complete step-by-step maintenance tasks through interactive checklists that can be linked to Work Orders, Assets, or PM Schedules.

### 1.1 Objectives

- Provide a structured way to define and track maintenance task completion
- Enable linking checklists to Work Orders for better task accountability
- Support optional linking to Assets and PM Schedules
- Track completion status with timestamps and user attribution
- Integrate seamlessly with existing RBAC and authentication systems

### 1.2 Scope

- **In Scope:** Checklist creation, item management, completion tracking, Work Order integration, API endpoints, frontend UI
- **Out of Scope:** Drag-and-drop reordering, checklist templates library, notifications, offline support

