## 3. Database Design

### 3.1 Database Schema

#### Table: `Checklists`

| Column | Type | Constraints | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|-------------|
| `id` | UUID | PK, DEFAULT UUIDV4 | Unique identifier |
| `org_id` | UUID | FK, NOT NULL | Organization reference |
| `work_order_id` | UUID | FK, NULLABLE | Optional Work Order link |
| `asset_id` | UUID | FK, NULLABLE | Optional Asset link |
| `pm_schedule_id` | UUID | FK, NULLABLE | Optional PM Schedule link |
| `name` | VARCHAR(255) | NOT NULL | Checklist name |
| `description` | TEXT | NULLABLE | Detailed description |
| `is_required` | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT FALSE | Must complete before WO completion |
| `is_active` | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT TRUE | Soft delete flag |
| `created_by` | UUID | FK, NOT NULL | User who created |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | DEFAULT NOW | Creation timestamp |
| `updated_at` | DATETIME | AUTO | Last update timestamp |
| `deleted_at` | DATETIME | NULLABLE | Soft delete timestamp |

#### Table: `ChecklistItems`

| Column | Type | Constraints | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|-------------|
| `id` | UUID | PK, DEFAULT UUIDV4 | Unique identifier |
| `checklist_id` | UUID | FK, NOT NULL | Parent checklist reference |
| `description` | VARCHAR(500) | NOT NULL | Task description |
| `order_index` | INT | DEFAULT 0 | Display order |
| `is_completed` | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT FALSE | Completion status |
| `completed_by` | UUID | FK, NULLABLE | User who completed |
| `completed_at` | DATETIME | NULLABLE | Completion timestamp |
| `notes` | TEXT | NULLABLE | Optional notes |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | DEFAULT NOW | Creation timestamp |
| `updated_at` | DATETIME | AUTO | Last update timestamp |
| `deleted_at` | DATETIME | NULLABLE | Soft delete timestamp |

### 3.2 Relationships

```
Organization (1) ──────────< (N) Checklists
WorkOrder (1) ────────────< (N) Checklists (optional)
Asset (1) ────────────────< (N) Checklists (optional)
PMSchedule (1) ───────────< (N) Checklists (optional)
User (1) ─────────────────< (N) Checklists (created_by)
Checklist (1) ────────────< (N) ChecklistItems
User (1) ─────────────────< (N) ChecklistItems (completed_by)
```

